If you read a ton of /x/ paranormal greentexts about hikers "innawoods" a surprising amount of them feature stuff like the other people on the trip having "relationship drama" between them, some couple having an argument, fight, etc. Generally conflicts, drama, discord, tensions.

All "negative emotions", spite, scandal between people (especially ones who otherwise love each other) release real material energy that begets, nourishes, and calls upon dark forces, like mosquitoes attracted to CO2. There is already enough Garmonbozia without our contributions.

Surely a large number of this is just fiction writers adding a psychological aspect to their anon story or people imitating earlier greentext classics, but there's also the other aspect that such animosity, enmity, hatred, etc. do invite and feed demonic creatures very literally.

Bodybuilding materializes one's way of life in a very comforting way. It's like those "Strange" weapons in Team Fortress 2 or StatTrak in Counter-Strike. When you have a hot dog with your friend you "know" it's going into your muscles. Everything leaves a reflection on your body.

E.g. you are playing badminton with your mother at the park and it's fun family time, but you're also aware it's "conditioning exercise", burning calories, improving ur cardio, etc. It makes you aware of your body no matter the context. Your physique is a sort of mnemonic device.

So every meal you eat, every activity you do, you are aware it leaves an impact on your physique. No experience is wasted this way. It's really soothing to people naturally prone to neuroticism and feeling that time is slipping away. Shane Hunt's video logs really show this well.
